G.3 verify (2026-05-14):

Scope: workspace-scoped outputs SSE stream so the desktop renders
       `output_dispatched`/`output_failed` toasts across all of a
       workspace's runs without subscribing per-run.

Files landed:
  api/src/routes/outputs-sse.ts        (NEW, ~135 lines)
  api/src/routes/outputs-sse.test.ts   (NEW, ~280 lines, 6 specs)
  api/src/app.ts                       (+2 lines: import + route mount)

Static checks:
  ✓ pnpm -F @basics/api exec vitest run src/routes/outputs-sse
        6/6 passing
  ✓ pnpm -F @basics/api exec vitest run (full suite)
        34 files / 294/294 passing
  ✓ pnpm -F @basics/api exec tsc --noEmit  clean

Route behavior:
  ✓ GET /v1/workspaces/:wsId/outputs/stream gated by the existing
    /v1/workspaces/* requireWorkspaceJwt middleware.
  ✓ Path :wsId cross-checked against jwt.workspace_id; mismatch
    returns 403 before any SSE stream is opened.
  ✓ Subscribes to Supabase Realtime on public.cloud_activity with
    filter `workspace_id=eq.<wsId>` for INSERT events. Filters
    `activity_type IN ('output_dispatched','output_failed')` in the
    JS callback (Realtime doesn't support IN expressions).
  ✓ On connect: emits one `event: ready` frame with the workspace_id
    so test clients (and the desktop) can tell the subscription is
    live before any output event arrives.
  ✓ Forwards each matching INSERT as `event: output` with payload:
    `{ run_id, kind, channel, to?, status, dispatched_at, error? }`.
  ✓ Field mapping handles production schema correctly (post-cycle-1
    fix):
      - dispatched: `to` ← payload.recipient_or_key (legacy `to`/
        `recipient` keys also tolerated for defense-in-depth)
      - failed: NO `to` field (production OutputFailedEventSchema
        has no recipient column; route doesn't fabricate one)
      - error: flattens `{code, message}` → message string for the
        toast; falls back to code; then literal "unknown" for
        malformed payloads
      - subject: dropped from the frame (never emitted by the
        worker; spec marked it "optional")
      - status: derived from activity_type ('dispatched' |
        'failed')
      - dispatched_at: row.created_at
  ✓ Keep-alive: `: keep-alive\n\n` comment frame every 25s; cleared
    on abort.
  ✓ Connection cleanup: stream.onAbort removes the supabase channel
    + clears keepalive.

Test seam:
  ✓ `setSupabaseFactoryForOutputsTests` exported with a distinct
    name (vs G.1's `setSupabaseFactoryForTests`) to avoid
    module-level state collision when both seam modules are loaded.

Test specs (all 6 green):
  1. "rejects request with no auth → 401" — middleware catch
  2. "rejects path workspace mismatch → 403" — JWT for ws A, path
      :wsId = ws B → 403
  3. "emits a ready frame on connect, then forwards
      output_dispatched (production payload shape) as event: output"
      — payload matches OutputDispatchedEventSchema:
      {kind, channel, recipient_or_key, content_hash, attempt,
       latency_ms} → frame has `to: recipient_or_key`
  4. "forwards output_failed (production payload shape) — flattens
      error.message; no recipient field" — payload matches
      OutputFailedEventSchema: {kind, channel, error:{code,message},
      retriable} → frame has flat error string, no `to`
  5. "IGNORES non-output activity_types (e.g. tool_call_start)" —
      ready frame still emitted but no `output` frame fires
  6. "tolerates legacy payload.to / payload.recipient keys as
      recipient fallbacks" — defensive against future schema
      renames

Adversarial review:
  Cycle 1 (review-1.json): verdict fix-blockers — caught two real
    blockers: (a) production output_dispatched payloads use
    `recipient_or_key`, not `to`/`recipient`, so the route's `to`
    field would have been undefined for every dispatched event;
    (b) output_failed payloads have NO recipient field at all, so
    `to`+`subject` would have been undefined for every failed
    event. Tests used fictional payload shapes that masked both
    bugs.
  Cycle 2 (review-2.json): verdict ship — 0 blockers; 4 nits
    (frame.kind echoes activity_type vs payload discriminator;
    legacy-key defense masks future renames; channel passed through
    unchecked; error fallback to 'unknown' rare).

Notes / decisions:
  - The route uses a single test seam name distinct from G.1's
    (`setSupabaseFactoryForOutputsTests` vs
    `setSupabaseFactoryForTests`) to avoid module-state collision
    if both seam modules are loaded by the same test process.
  - Error field is flattened (string) rather than passed through as
    {code, message} so the desktop toast can render
    "email failed: SES throttled the request" without conditional
    rendering logic on the client.
  - No hydrate frame — outputs are time-sensitive notifications, not
    state to catch up on. The `ready` frame signals subscription
    liveness only.
  - cloud_activity is INSERT-only; no UPDATE/DELETE forwarding
    needed (different from G.1 which forwards all three on the
    approvals table).

Out of scope (lands in G.4):
  - Combined dual-channel approval live e2e (desktop + SMS + outputs
    all firing on one operator-driven walkthrough).
